{
  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Geeta @ Reeta Mishra versus Ajay Kumar Mishra  pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_9_640_644','2025INSC1102'); ><font size='4'> <strong>GEETA @ REETA MISHRA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>AJAY KUMAR MISHRA  </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 640</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1102</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004032025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The High Court has affirmed the decree of divorce granted by the Family Court vide order dated 20.09.2019. Whether respondent- husband should contribute towards the marriage expenses of his daughter. Headnotes&dagger; Hindu Marriage Act, 1955 &ndash; s.13(1)(ia) &ndash; Family Court granted divorce on grounds of cruelty &ndash; The High Court, by the impugned judgment, affirmed the decree of divorce &ndash; Before this Court, the appellant-wife has confined her claim to seeking an amount of Rs.10,00,000/- towards the marriage expenses of their daughter: Held: It<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 12-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 11787/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_9_640_644','2025INSC1102','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href